Alternatively,&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flowering_plant" target="_blank">Angiosperms</a>,&nbsp;the flowering plants, have only a small subgroup that exhibit either separate male and female flowers or separate male and female plants, and instead most angiosperms are <a href="http://bioimages.vanderbilt.edu/pages/sexual-systems.htm" target="_blank">hermaphrodites</a>, meaning all of their flowers contain both male and female sex organs.<br />
